Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
unlockOaDesign(25.10)                                    unlockOaDesign(25.10)

Name
       unlockOaDesign - Unlocks the specified OpenAccess design

Syntax
       unlockOaDesign

       [-help]

       <lib>

       <cell>

       <view>

       Unlocks the specified OpenAccess design.

       A  design  cannot  be opened if setOaxMode -locking is set to true, and
       the design is currently locked. You can use the unlockOaDesign  command
       to  free the lock so that other tools can access and edit the database.
       You also can use the command to override the lock, if the design is in-
       correctly locked.

       You can use the unlockOaDesign command at any time.

Parameters
       <cell> Specifies the name of the top cell to unlock.

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each unlockOaDesign parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man unlockOaDesign.

       <lib>  Specifies the name of the OpenAccess library in which the design
              was saved.

       <view> Specifies the name of the cell view to unlock.

Example
              * The  following  command  unlocks  the  view layout in the cell
                dtmf_chip in the library designLib:

                unlockOaDesign designLib dtmf_chip layout

Related Information
              * setOaxMode

